# Ollama Modelfile for Arabic-GLM-OCR-v2
#
# ============================================================================
#  IMPORTANT — KNOWN OLLAMA LIMITATION FOR THIS MODEL
# ============================================================================
#
# Arabic-GLM-OCR-v2 is a vision-language model (it sees images and emits text).
# Ollama's Modelfile syntax does NOT support attaching a separate vision
# projector ("mmproj") to a custom GGUF, so even if you import the
# community-converted GGUF, the resulting Ollama model will lack vision
# capability and OCR will not work. See:
#   https://github.com/ollama/ollama/issues/9967
#   https://github.com/ollama/ollama/blob/main/docs/modelfile.mdx
#
# Three working options for running the Arabic model on Windows / Linux:
#
#   1. Single-model fallback (immediate, no extra setup):
#        - Use the registry 'glm-ocr' model for both languages.
#        - Run:
#            python -m pharma_ocr.cli process --input file.pdf \
#                --ar-model glm-ocr --en-model glm-ocr
#        - Or, for the API server:
#            set PHARMOCR_AR_MODEL=glm-ocr        (PowerShell: $env:PHARMOCR_AR_MODEL = "glm-ocr")
#        - Trade-off: lower Arabic accuracy than the fine-tune, but works today.
#
#   2. Hugging Face transformers backend (high-accuracy Arabic):
#        - Install: pip install torch torchvision transformers accelerate
#        - Set PHARMOCR_AR_BACKEND=hf and download safetensors from:
#            huggingface-cli download sherif1313/Arabic-GLM-OCR-v2 \
#                --local-dir ./models/arabic-glm-ocr
#        - The Arabic client will load the model in-process via transformers,
#          bypassing Ollama entirely for this language.
#
#   3. llama-server (llama.cpp) for the Arabic model:
#        - Download both the language GGUF and the mmproj from
#            https://huggingface.co/Makadi86/Arabic-GLM-OCR-v2-GGUF
#        - Run: llama-server -m arabic-glm-ocr-v2-fixed.gguf \
#                            --mmproj mmproj-arabic-glm-ocr-v2.gguf --port 8080
#        - Set PHARMOCR_AR_BACKEND=llamacpp and PHARMOCR_AR_URL=http://localhost:8080
#
# This Modelfile remains in the repo as a placeholder for the day Ollama
# supports custom vision GGUFs. Until then, prefer options (1)–(3) above.
#
# ============================================================================
#
# If you still want to attempt the import (it will succeed but the resulting
# model will lack vision), edit the FROM line below to point to your local
# GGUF and run:
#   ollama create arabic-glm-ocr -f ollama/Modelfile.arabic-glm-ocr

FROM ./models/arabic-glm-ocr/arabic-glm-ocr-v2-fixed.gguf

# Pure greedy decoding — Arabic OCR errors compound very fast with sampling
PARAMETER temperature 0
PARAMETER top_p 1
PARAMETER top_k 1
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.0

PARAMETER num_predict 4096
PARAMETER num_ctx 8192

# Arabic system prompt — primes the model for Arabic pharma RTL extraction
SYSTEM """
أنت محرك OCR متخصص في النشرات الدوائية والمستندات التنظيمية.
استخرج كل نص ظاهر في الصورة كما هو بدقة تامة، مع الحفاظ على:
  - الجداول بصيغة Markdown.
  - عناوين الأقسام (مثل: المؤشرات، الجرعة، موانع الاستعمال).
  - الأرقام والوحدات كما هي مطبوعة (مجم، ملغ، مل، وحدة دولية).
لا تترجم، ولا تلخص، ولا تعيد صياغة النص. أخرج النص المستخرج فقط.
"""
